default5.3default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultA comparison of median rents across Broad Rental Market Areas and LHA rates shows that a family renting a typical three bedroom home would have to make up more than £100 a month in over a quarter (27%) of loca
defaultl authority areas in England if the 13 week protection rule is abolished. In more than two in five (43%) of local authorities families will have a shortfall of more than £75 a month.
